  "texts": [
    "Thus, only the function Q(s, a, Θ) has its parameters Θ updated by backpropagation.",
    "The parameters Θ are updated directly (i.e., copied) from the values of Θ with a certain frequency, remaining unchanged between two consecutive updates.",
    "Thus, only the forward pass is performed when the network is used with the parameters Θ to predict the value of the target function.",
    "Specifi- cally, at each time-step t, a transition (or experience) is defined by a tuple τ t = (s t, a t, r t, s t+1), in which s t is the current state, a t is the action taken at that state, r t is the reward received at t, and s t+1 is the state resulting after taking action a t.",
    "Recent experiences are stored to con- struct a replay buffer D = {τ 1, τ 2,."
